  "text": "If the kernel k is strictly positive definite, system (11) admits a unique solution as the system matrix k(X, X) is regular. Therefore, an interpolant is always well defined even if the right hand side in [CITATION_1] does not stem from the evaluation of a function f ∈ H on the set of centers X. In cases where the kernel is only positive definite, i.e. k(X, X) is positive semi-definite, the system has in general no unique solution for arbitrary right hand sides. However, a solution still exists when f ∈ H:",
